1
00:00:29,620 --> 00:00:32,980
=The Secret of the Lost Pearl=

2
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:34,940
=Episode 16=
(Fiction. Do not imitate.)

3
00:00:42,790 --> 00:00:43,880
That's pretty nice.

4
00:00:45,750 --> 00:00:46,590
Lu,

5
00:00:47,390 --> 00:00:48,750
as you always say,

6
00:00:48,920 --> 00:00:50,670
better safe than sorry.

7
00:00:51,070 --> 00:00:53,200
The door opened so easily.

8
00:00:53,350 --> 00:00:55,150
I think something's off.

9
00:00:55,320 --> 00:00:56,520
We should be careful.

10
00:01:01,750 --> 00:01:02,640
Give me a hand.

11
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:15,960
It's safe now.

12
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:17,040
Let's go.

13
00:01:37,870 --> 00:01:39,870
This place is really run-down.

14
00:01:39,950 --> 00:01:42,120
Not a single burial item in this room.

15
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,430
The walls are plain.

16
00:01:43,870 --> 00:01:45,120
Not even any carvings.

17
00:01:45,120 --> 00:01:47,040
I think it's worse
than that fake main hall.

18
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,040
Don't shout.

19
00:01:48,350 --> 00:01:49,230
Look at this.

20
00:01:49,590 --> 00:01:50,430
What is it?

21
00:01:51,510 --> 00:01:53,200
This tomb owner is interesting.

22
00:01:53,310 --> 00:01:55,150
He even buried chime bells with him.

23
00:01:55,590 --> 00:01:57,510
What's so interesting

24
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:58,920
about burying a few bells?

25
00:01:59,150 --> 00:02:00,130
Chime bells were popular

26
00:02:00,870 --> 00:02:02,150
during the Western Zhou.

27
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:05,510
Back then, only the emperor
could enjoy music.

28
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:07,640
But by the late Western Zhou,

29
00:02:07,802 --> 00:02:09,001
the rules became more relaxed.

30
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:11,120
These feudal lords

31
00:02:11,463 --> 00:02:12,560
started copying the emperor.

32
00:02:12,560 --> 00:02:13,520
Wait, hold on.

33
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:15,520
Wasn't it Tang just now?

34
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:17,430
Why are we back to the Western Zhou?

35
00:02:17,833 --> 00:02:18,747
We've walked this far;

36
00:02:18,758 --> 00:02:20,549
you still think this is
a Western Zhou tomb?

37
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:21,710
So, it's Tang?

38
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:26,590
Haven't you figured it out yet?

39
00:02:27,430 --> 00:02:30,280
This tomb belongs

40
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:31,710
to both dynasties.

41
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:34,190
From my observation,

42
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:36,870
this was originally a Western Zhou tomb.

43
00:02:37,310 --> 00:02:38,800
Later, Tang builders

44
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:40,560
renovated it on that foundation.

45
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:42,840
So, the structure and size

46
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:44,033
are in the Western Zhou style,

47
00:02:44,430 --> 00:02:47,000
but the internal design
is in the Tang style.

48
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:50,000
So, those people couldn't find

49
00:02:50,190 --> 00:02:52,030
another good burial site?

50
00:02:52,030 --> 00:02:53,520
They had to use this same spot?

51
00:02:53,910 --> 00:02:56,520
That just proves
the Feng Shui here is excellent.

52
00:02:56,590 --> 00:02:59,360
The Feng Shui must be good.

53
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:01,590
But these chime bells

54
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,800
look a bit strange.

55
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:05,800
Why?

56
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,520
I've seen good chime bells before.

57
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:09,560
At the museum.

58
00:03:09,630 --> 00:03:11,150
The Zeng Houyi Chime Bells

59
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:13,630
were unearthed in Sui County,
Hubei, in 1978.

60
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:14,910
That set

61
00:03:15,750 --> 00:03:17,280
had 65 bells.

62
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:20,560
The range alone spanned 5.5 octaves.

63
00:03:20,710 --> 00:03:21,710
When played,

64
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:23,430
it sounded like a symphony.

65
00:03:23,910 --> 00:03:24,840
But look at these.

66
00:03:25,470 --> 00:03:26,710
Only two rows hanging here.

67
00:03:27,430 --> 00:03:28,596
This is like a scrawny donkey

68
00:03:29,310 --> 00:03:31,590
forcing out a hard load.

69
00:03:31,590 --> 00:03:32,373
You cultured folks

70
00:03:32,384 --> 00:03:33,509
have completely confused me.

71
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:34,360
If you ask me,

72
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:36,520
let's just pry it open

73
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:37,870
and see who's lying inside

74
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:39,150
to know what's going on.

75
00:03:41,190 --> 00:03:42,030
Light the candle.

76
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:53,120
Come on. One, two, three.

77
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:03,680
Use the tools.

78
00:04:17,190 --> 00:04:18,830
Why did this piece fall off?

79
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:21,000
You must have shaken it loose.

80
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:21,850
Nonsense.

81
00:04:21,870 --> 00:04:23,070
We pried from this side.

82
00:04:23,081 --> 00:04:24,367
Why would it crumble over there?

83
00:04:25,310 --> 00:04:26,160
Here's another piece.

84
00:04:27,390 --> 00:04:28,430
There's more over here.

85
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:36,360
These fragments are the same size.

86
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:37,390
The edges are clean.

87
00:04:38,190 --> 00:04:39,876
They probably didn't fall off
by accident.

88
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:42,310
I have a different one.

89
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:43,560
Look, this one's square.

90
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:48,480
Usually, when strange things happen
while opening a coffin,

91
00:04:48,870 --> 00:04:51,070
it means there's a trap

92
00:04:51,310 --> 00:04:52,510
to stop tomb raiders.

93
00:04:53,270 --> 00:04:55,630
But these fragments...

94
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:01,120
What are they for?

95
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:02,960
Chubby,

96
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:05,270
when we opened the coffin just now,

97
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:06,390
did you feel anything?

98
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:09,870
It felt like someone inside
was pulling hard,

99
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,526
as if they didn't want me to open it.

100
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:12,400
I felt that too.

101
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:14,480
Normally,

102
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:16,600
coffins are shut from the outside.

103
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,333
There shouldn't be force from inside.

104
00:05:18,950 --> 00:05:20,000
Unless...

105
00:05:22,510 --> 00:05:24,750
Unless there's

106
00:05:25,070 --> 00:05:26,390
a thousand-year-old corpse?

107
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:28,120
Don't panic.

108
00:05:28,510 --> 00:05:29,830
What Chen means is

109
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:32,720
that there may be a mechanism inside.

110
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:34,560
Inside?

111
00:05:34,750 --> 00:05:35,590
Yes.

112
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:37,390
Only if the mechanism is inside

113
00:05:37,430 --> 00:05:38,870
would we feel resistance

114
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:40,480
when opening it.

115
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:41,800
Impossible.

116
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:44,000
Who'd install a mechanism inside?

117
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:45,600
The guy lying in there?

118
00:05:50,510 --> 00:05:52,160
One, two, three, four, five.

119
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:54,160
These five fragments

120
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:55,870
seem to fit perfectly

121
00:05:55,870 --> 00:05:57,190
into those grooves.

122
00:05:58,630 --> 00:05:59,470
Let me see.

123
00:05:59,823 --> 00:06:00,943
- Let me see.
- Put them in.

124
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:02,720
Maybe the coffin will open.

125
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,920
That's easy.

126
00:06:04,310 --> 00:06:05,510
It's just like a puzzle.

127
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:07,680
Just piece them together.

128
00:06:09,270 --> 00:06:10,600
Put the square one in that slot.

129
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:27,430
It's not moving.

130
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:58,983
The candle is out. The ghost...

131
00:06:58,994 --> 00:07:00,190
The ghost blew out the candle.

132
00:07:04,310 --> 00:07:05,150
Lu!

133
00:07:13,510 --> 00:07:14,350
Lu.

134
00:07:16,830 --> 00:07:17,670
This...

135
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:20,430
What's going on with the fire?

136
00:07:26,310 --> 00:07:28,510
Did we arrange those bronze pieces wrong

137
00:07:28,510 --> 00:07:29,560
and trigger a mechanism?

138
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:30,586
That's white phosphorus.

139
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:31,950
It ignites with friction.

140
00:07:36,310 --> 00:07:37,510
It's all your fault, Chubby.

141
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:39,240
Why are your hands so itchy?

142
00:07:39,270 --> 00:07:40,712
If you're talking about mechanisms,

143
00:07:40,723 --> 00:07:41,560
ask Chen.

144
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:42,750
Why blame me?

145
00:07:42,750 --> 00:07:44,160
It was Ms. He's idea.

146
00:07:44,160 --> 00:07:45,430
I was just helping.

147
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:46,600
Shifting blame now, huh?

148
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:47,800
- You did it.
- Come on.

149
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:49,750
Even if we cross this trench,

150
00:07:49,870 --> 00:07:50,790
we still can't get out.

151
00:07:51,070 --> 00:07:51,920
Why?

152
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:55,520
Where's the door?

153
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:03,070
Why is there suddenly a wall?

154
00:08:03,480 --> 00:08:04,870
What kind of mechanism is this?

155
00:08:06,510 --> 00:08:07,600
Forget that for now.

156
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:09,266
The fire is getting stronger.

157
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:10,800
The oxygen will run out.

158
00:08:11,190 --> 00:08:12,303
We need to put out the fire.

159
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:14,160
How do we put out a fire this big?

160
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:15,510
The only way now

161
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:17,830
is to seal the fire
under the stone slab.

162
00:08:18,070 --> 00:08:19,040
Once the oxygen is gone,

163
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:20,393
the fire will go out by itself.

164
00:08:21,870 --> 00:08:22,950
What we need to do now

165
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,062
is arrange these fragments

166
00:08:24,073 --> 00:08:25,310
in the correct way.

167
00:08:25,390 --> 00:08:26,230
Rearrange them.

168
00:08:27,190 --> 00:08:29,830
The square one goes in the middle.

169
00:08:30,390 --> 00:08:31,390
As for the other four,

170
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:32,926
they seem about the same anywhere.

171
00:08:33,150 --> 00:08:34,390
Four fragments can be arranged

172
00:08:34,630 --> 00:08:35,600
in 24 combinations.

173
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,120
Now, there are 23 left.

174
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:38,146
Let's try them one by one.

175
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:45,920
Look.

176
00:08:46,790 --> 00:08:48,323
The middle one looks like a character.

177
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:51,240
This is bronze script.

178
00:08:51,856 --> 00:08:53,150
Mine has the character for Metal.

179
00:08:53,150 --> 00:08:54,200
Mine is Fire.

180
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:56,320
This one is Earth.

181
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:58,573
These are the five elements.

182
00:08:58,870 --> 00:08:59,710
This one is Wood.

183
00:09:01,790 --> 00:09:02,790
Wood generates Fire.

184
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:05,550
Fire generates Earth.

185
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,120
Earth generates Metal.

186
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:08,240
Metal generates Water.

187
00:09:23,390 --> 00:09:24,270
No, no.

188
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:25,200
No.

189
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:26,720
Chen, it's worse now.

190
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:28,200
- Take them off.
- Hurry.

191
00:09:28,670 --> 00:09:29,550
Think of something.

192
00:09:30,310 --> 00:09:31,150
Turn them over.

193
00:09:31,150 --> 00:09:32,910
Arrange them again by mutual restraint.

194
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:33,692
Mutual restraint?

195
00:09:33,703 --> 00:09:34,750
If generation didn't work,

196
00:09:34,750 --> 00:09:35,720
why would restraint work?

197
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:36,720
We still have to try.

198
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:38,030
We can't just stand here.

199
00:09:38,030 --> 00:09:40,030
No. We can't keep trying.

200
00:09:40,390 --> 00:09:42,630
Every mistake makes the fire bigger.

201
00:09:43,030 --> 00:09:44,630
We don't have time for more errors.

202
00:09:46,630 --> 00:09:47,670
Then what do we do?

203
00:09:52,790 --> 00:09:53,630
Wait.

204
00:09:55,510 --> 00:09:56,630
Turn all the fragments over.

205
00:09:56,790 --> 00:09:58,200
- Turn them over?
- Do as I say.

206
00:09:58,200 --> 00:09:59,040
Hurry.

207
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,440
And then?

208
00:10:01,630 --> 00:10:02,470
Then...

209
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:03,840
Untie me. I'll do it myself.

210
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:08,270
Commander Chen?

211
00:10:08,510 --> 00:10:09,350
Untie her.

212
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:27,200
What pattern is this?

213
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:02,840
It's closed.

214
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,000
Did it work?

215
00:11:09,270 --> 00:11:10,240
Is it safe now?

216
00:11:10,690 --> 00:11:11,550
You idiot.

217
00:11:11,550 --> 00:11:12,870
Why are you so rough?

218
00:11:12,870 --> 00:11:14,840
Look how scared you were.
I knew it was fine.

219
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:16,440
- Don't come over.
- What's wrong?

220
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:18,150
You're too heavy. It might collapse.

221
00:11:18,670 --> 00:11:20,000
Collapse?

222
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:21,320
Go away.

223
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:22,160
Stay away from me.

224
00:11:23,150 --> 00:11:24,080
So annoying.

225
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,720
Miss Bai, I didn't expect you

226
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:49,120
to have this kind of talent.

227
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:50,510
You're truly versatile.

228
00:11:50,670 --> 00:11:52,790
We should've untied you sooner.

229
00:11:54,790 --> 00:11:55,870
I only just thought of it.

230
00:11:57,240 --> 00:11:58,750
What pattern did you arrange just now?

231
00:11:59,870 --> 00:12:02,200
You seem to know this tomb pretty well.

232
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:04,270
Let's not talk about that now.

233
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:05,150
The fire was huge.

234
00:12:05,150 --> 00:12:05,893
The oxygen is low.

235
00:12:05,904 --> 00:12:06,989
Let's find a way out first.

236
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:07,840
How's your side?

237
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,320
The wall is solid.

238
00:12:09,790 --> 00:12:11,120
I can't move it at all.

239
00:12:11,510 --> 00:12:12,390
Same here.

240
00:12:14,750 --> 00:12:15,770
- Look.
- We're finished.

241
00:12:18,150 --> 00:12:19,440
The fire's out,

242
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:21,120
but the doors are sealed.

243
00:12:21,390 --> 00:12:23,960
It's like trapping a turtle
behind closed doors.

244
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:24,830
Get lost.

245
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:26,270
Can you shut up?

246
00:12:26,270 --> 00:12:27,390
You're the turtle.

247
00:12:27,563 --> 00:12:28,896
I'll use the light to dazzle you.

248
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:32,560
Miss Bai,

249
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:34,320
since you managed

250
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:35,630
to open this mechanism,

251
00:12:35,960 --> 00:12:37,150
can you also

252
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:39,080
open this door?

253
00:12:40,030 --> 00:12:41,630
If I could,

254
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:43,750
I wouldn't be trapped here with you.

255
00:12:48,853 --> 00:12:50,469
There's always a solution to mechanisms.

256
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:51,790
There must be a way out.

257
00:12:52,750 --> 00:12:53,960
We need to hurry.

258
00:12:54,016 --> 00:12:55,030
I've only bumped the wall,

259
00:12:55,030 --> 00:12:56,139
and I'm short of breath.

260
00:12:56,150 --> 00:12:57,200
The oxygen in here

261
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:58,270
won't last long.

262
00:12:58,750 --> 00:12:59,840
If this keeps up,

263
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:02,740
we'll be buried here
with the guy in that coffin.

264
00:13:02,750 --> 00:13:03,316
Nonsense.

265
00:13:03,327 --> 00:13:04,829
We just unlocked the coffin mechanism.

266
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:05,690
Open it again.

267
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:06,750
Alright. Open it.

268
00:13:06,870 --> 00:13:08,000
Open it again?

269
00:13:08,150 --> 00:13:10,120
The mechanism might be
inside the coffin.

270
00:13:10,150 --> 00:13:11,150
Do whatever you want.

271
00:13:11,150 --> 00:13:11,990
Light the candle.

272
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:14,270
Fine. Go open it.

273
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:29,200
One, two, three.

274
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:46,910
A whole vat of mercury.

275
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:50,820
- Keep going.
- Come on.

276
00:13:59,870 --> 00:14:00,960
The Hercules Cup.

277
00:14:03,240 --> 00:14:04,270
Look at his hand.

278
00:14:04,670 --> 00:14:06,183
There's also an eyeball pattern on it.

279
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:07,320
Chen, over here.

280
00:14:07,653 --> 00:14:08,773
You can see it clearly here.

281
00:14:09,080 --> 00:14:09,920
Look.

282
00:14:13,480 --> 00:14:15,030
Look at his hand. It's green.

283
00:14:15,360 --> 00:14:16,600
What's wrong with your eyes?

284
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:18,550
That's bronze. It's oxidized.

285
00:14:20,510 --> 00:14:21,350
Careful.

286
00:14:32,870 --> 00:14:34,000
Look at that wall.

287
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:53,080
We must've triggered the mechanism

288
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:54,320
when we took the cuju ball.

289
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:56,150
But this mechanism

290
00:14:56,240 --> 00:14:57,840
didn't harm us at all.

291
